  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0db9\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a\u0db1 \u0d91\u0dc3\u0dca.\u0d91\u0dc3\u0dca.\u0db4\u0dd3\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d87\u0db4 \u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rambukkana SSP's bail granted by Attorney General",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Kegalle SSP K. Wijewardena has been remanded in connection with the Rambukkana shooting incident. B. The Attorney General informed the Court of Appeal today (27) that he was opposed to the release on bail of Keerthiratne and four other police officers.",
        "Deputy Solicitor General Janaka Bandara, appearing before the Court of Appeal on behalf of the Attorney General, said, B. Keerthiratne and four other police officers filed a fundamental rights petition in court.",
        "The writ petition was heard by a bench of Justices of the Court of Appeal comprising Sobhitha Rajakaruna and Dhammika Ganepola today (27).",
        "Accordingly, the petition was scheduled to be reconsidered on the 29th.",
        "Former SSP in charge of Kegalle Division K. B. The writ petition filed by Mr. Keerthiratne and three other police constables named the Attorney General, the Inspector General of Police and the Director of the CID as respondents.",
        "The petitioners have stated that the order issued by the Kegalle Magistrate to arrest and remand them in connection with the shooting death of a person during a riot that took place during a protest in Rambukkana regarding the increase in fuel prices is against the law."
      ],
